No. 764,

October Term, 1954.

Hupman v. United States. Frank J. Donner, Arthur Kinoy and Marshall Perlin for movant-petitioner. Solicitor General Rankin filed a memorandum for the United States in opposition.

The motion to vacate orders denying petition for writ of certiorari, 349 U. S. 953, and petition for rehearing, 350 U. S. 855, is denied.
